{"title_page": "Quality of Life Program 2020 (Saudi Arabia)", "text_new": "{{Infobox organization\n| name = Quality of Life Program 2020\n| formation = 2018\n| type = Governmental program\n| affiliations = [[Saudi Vision 2030]]\n| budget = $34.6 billion.\n| website = {{URL|https://vision2030.gov.sa/en/programs/QoL|vision2030.gov.sa}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Quality of Life Program 2020''' is one of the [[Saudi Vision 2030]] realization programs with a general aim of improving the individual's lifestyle in [[Saudi Arabia]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://vision2030.gov.sa/en/programs/QoL|title=Quality of Life Program {{!}} Saudi Vision 2030|website=vision2030.gov.sa|access-date=2019-07-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-saudi-entertainment-idUSKBN1I42PM|title=Saudi Arabia launches initiative to improve country's lifestyle|date=2018-05-04|work=Reuters|access-date=2019-07-07|language=en}}</ref> The improvements include developing an ecosystem to support the participation of citizens and residents in cultural, environment, and sports activities.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/business/economy/2018/05/03/Saudi-Arabia-launches-34-6-bln-Quality-of-Life-Program-2020.html|title=Saudi Arabia launches $34.6 bln Quality of Life Program 2020|website=english.alarabiya.net|language=en|access-date=2019-07-04}}</ref> The program was launched in May 2018 with a total budget of $35 billion.<ref name=\"Arabnews\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.arabnews.com/node/1296076/saudi-arabia|title=Kingdom\u2019s Council for Economic Development to spend $35bn on Saudi lifestyles by 2020|date=2018-05-03|website=Arab News|language=en|access-date=2019-07-04}}</ref>\n\n== Objectives ==\nThe program gives its main objectives as:<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\"Arabnews\" />{{third-party inline|reason=government-controlled media|date=January 2020}}\n\n* Enhancing the participation of citizens and residents in sports and athletic activities.\n* Reaching excellence achieved regionally and globally in some chosen professional sports.\n* Developing and diversifying entertainment opportunities in order to meet the population's needs.\n\n== Commitments ==\nOne of the commitments of this program is the opening of more than 45 cinemas in the country after the 35-year ban on cinemas was lifted.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/apr/20/saudi-arabias-first-cinema-in-over-35-years-opens-with-black-panther|title=Saudi Arabia's first cinema in over 35 years opens with Black Panther|last=France-Presse|first=Agence|date=2018-04-20|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-07-07|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" /> The commitments also include developing art galleries, museums, public libraries theaters, and an opera house.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== External links ==\n\n* [https://vision2030.gov.sa/sites/default/files/attachments/QoL%20English_0.pdf Quality of Life Program 2020 (Delivery plan).]\n\n== References ==\n<references />{{portal|Saudi Arabia}}\n\n__FORCETOC__\n\n[[Category:Saudi Arabian society]]\n[[Category:Future vision statements of countries]]\n\n\n{{SaudiArabia-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox organization\n| name = Quality of Life Program 2020\n| formation = 2018\n| type = Governmental program\n| affiliations = [[Saudi Vision 2030]]\n| budget = $34.6 billion.\n| website = {{URL|https://vision2030.gov.sa/en/programs/QoL|vision2030.gov.sa}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Quality of Life Program 2020''' is one of the [[Saudi Vision 2030]] realization programs with a general aim of improving the individual's lifestyle in [[Saudi Arabia]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://vision2030.gov.sa/en/programs/QoL|title=Quality of Life Program {{!}} Saudi Vision 2030|website=vision2030.gov.sa|access-date=2019-07-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-saudi-entertainment-idUSKBN1I42PM|title=Saudi Arabia launches initiative to improve country's lifestyle|date=2018-0