{"title_page": "Wadi Al Disah", "text_new": "{{short description|Geographic area in Tabuk, Saudi Arabia}}\n{{Orphan|date=April 2019}}\n\n'''Wadi Al Disah''' is a mountainous area located in the southwest Province of [[Tabuk, Saudi Arabia]].<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.argaam.com/en/article/articledetail/id/581826|title=PIF launches development project to boost sustainable tourism|website=ArgaamPlus|language=en|access-date=2019-04-13}}</ref> It is 4000 square meters away from Tabuk.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.seesaudi.sa/english/pages/PhotoDetails.aspx?PhotoId=85b4afec-d59f-4340-9d95-2074a71963d6|title=Nature in Wadi Al Dessah Tabuk region|website=www.seesaudi.sa|access-date=2019-04-13}}</ref> Wadi Al Disah is mainly located in the [[Mohammad bin Salman|Prince Mohammed bin Salman]] Natural Reserve.<ref name=\"auto\"/> The weather of the area is warm during summers and mild during winter which makes it a suitable area for planting. The village of Disah itself has many ancient remains that are traced back to the [[Nabataeans|Nabateen]] era.<ref name=\"auto1\"/> As Al Disah has a number of ancient buildings, many of those buildings contain Arabic writings.<ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n\n== Development Project ==\nIn an aim at boosting tourism is Saudi Arabia, the [[Public Investment Fund of Saudi Arabia|Public Investment Fund]] (PIF) has launched a development project to improve Wadi Al Disah and prepare it for local and international tourism. The project opts to make the area the most environmental diversified destination in Saudi Arabia.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Portal|Saudi Arabia}}\n\n[[Category:Geography of Saudi Arabia]]\n\n\n{{SaudiArabia-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Geographic area in Tabuk, Saudi Arabia}}\n{{Orphan|date=April 2019}}\n\n'''Wadi Al Disah''' is a mountainous area located in the southwest Province of [[Tabuk, Saudi Arabia]].<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.argaam.com/en/article/articledetail/id/581826|title=PIF launches development project to boost sustainable tourism|website=ArgaamPlus|language=en|access-date=2019-04-13}}</ref> It is 4000 square meters away from Tabuk.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.seesaudi.sa/english/pages/PhotoDetails.aspx?PhotoId=85b4afec-d59f-4340-9d95-2074a71963d6|title=Nature in Wadi Al Dessah Tabuk region|website=www.seesaudi.sa|access-date=2019-04-13}}</ref> Wadi Al Disah is mainly located in the [[Mohammad bin Salman|Prince Mohammed bin Salman]] Natural Reserve.<ref name=\"auto\"/> The weather of the area is warm during summers and mild during winter which makes it a suitable area for planting. The village of Disah itself has many ancient remains that are traced back to the [[Nabataeans|Nabateen]] era.<ref name=\"auto1\"/> As Al Disah has a number of ancient buildings, many of those buildings contain Arabic writings.<ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n\n== Development Project ==\nIn an aim at boosting tourism is Saudi Arabia, the [[Public Investment Fund of Saudi Arabia|Public Investment Fund]] (PIF) has launched a development project to improve Wadi Al Disah and prepare it for local and international tourism. The project opts to make the area the most environmental diversified destination in Saudi Arabia.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Portal|Saudi Arabia}}\n\n[[Category:Geography of Saudi Arabia]]\n[[Category:Saudi Arabia stubs]]\n", "name_user": "Joeykai", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wadi_Al_Disah"}
